Setting up Git along with GitHib

1.  Set a Git username
    git config --global user.name "Saurav Agarwal"

2.  Set a Git user email
    git config --global user.email "agr.saurav1@gmail.com"

3.  Generate a new SSH key for GitHub
    ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096 -C "agr.saurav1@gmail.com"

4.  eval "$(ssh-agent -s)"

5.  ssh-add ~/.ssh/id_rsa

6.  sudo apt install xclip

7.  xclip -sel clip < ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub

6.  Alternate: Copy using text editor

7.  Go to settings in the GitHub profile and add new SSH key

8.  git config --global core.editor "vim"
